{"title": "Lec-61: What is Routing Protocols | Various types of Routing Protocols", "lang": "en", "segments": [{"start": 0.307, "dur": 2.02, "text": "Hello friends! Welcome to Gate Smashers."}, {"start": 2.627, "dur": 1.093, "text": "In today's video we will"}, {"start": 3.753, "dur": 1.007, "text": "discuss about"}, {"start": 4.793, "dur": 1.12, "text": "routing protocols and"}, {"start": 6.187, "dur": 1.006, "text": "its categorization."}, {"start": 7.253, "dur": 1.5, "text": "So what is routing protocol."}, {"start": 8.787, "dur": 1.166, "text": "And what are its"}, {"start": 9.987, "dur": 1.006, "text": "different categories."}, {"start": 11.307, "dur": 1.673, "text": "We are going to discuss about this."}, {"start": 13.247, "dur": 2.026, "text": "But before that I want to tell you that what"}, {"start": 15.307, "dur": 1.006, "text": "is major functionality of"}, {"start": 16.42, "dur": 1.84, "text": "network layer."}, {"start": 18.653, "dur": 1.9, "text": "Forwarding."}, {"start": 20.653, "dur": 1.2, "text": "Forwarding the packet."}, {"start": 21.893, "dur": 1.787, "text": "What is the meaning of forwarding the"}, {"start": 23.88, "dur": 1.233, "text": "To put the packet on"}, {"start": 25.247, "dur": 1.26, "text": "its right path is"}, {"start": 26.54, "dur": 1.007, "text": "forwarding."}, {"start": 27.733, "dur": 1.874, "text": "Basically, who does the forwarding?"}, {"start": 29.927, "dur": 1.006, "text": "Let's say"}, {"start": 31.233, "dur": 2.394, "text": "There is a router"}, {"start": 33.687, "dur": 1.473, "text": "And router generally, in network, is"}, {"start": 35.193, "dur": 1.007, "text": "connected to multiple networks."}, {"start": 36.54, "dur": 1.12, "text": "So let's say router is connected to"}, {"start": 37.693, "dur": 1.914, "text": "To N1."}, {"start": 40.28, "dur": 1.007, "text": "To N2."}, {"start": 41.833, "dur": 1.007, "text": "To N3."}, {"start": 43.333, "dur": 1.66, "text": "To N4"}, {"start": 45.027, "dur": 1.113, "text": "It is connected to multiple networks."}, {"start": 46.173, "dur": 2.88, "text": "Now any packet. Let's say, a packet arrives."}, {"start": 49.373, "dur": 1.007, "text": "The packet is received by"}, {"start": 50.427, "dur": 1.233, "text": "router."}, {"start": 51.693, "dur": 1.807, "text": "After receiving the packet."}, {"start": 53.873, "dur": 1.294, "text": "It will open the"}, {"start": 55.2, "dur": 1.087, "text": "packet internally and"}, {"start": 56.547, "dur": 1.053, "text": "send it on the"}, {"start": 57.64, "dur": 1.007, "text": "right path."}, {"start": 58.72, "dur": 1.613, "text": "And basically,"}, {"start": 60.367, "dur": 1.24, "text": "what is the right path?"}, {"start": 61.64, "dur": 1.007, "text": "It should be optimal path."}, {"start": 62.68, "dur": 1.147, "text": "Optimal means"}, {"start": 63.86, "dur": 1.707, "text": "the shortest path"}, {"start": 65.873, "dur": 1.314, "text": "with lesser delay."}, {"start": 67.48, "dur": 2.207, "text": "Cost should also be less."}, {"start": 69.72, "dur": 1.273, "text": "Packet should reach quickly."}, {"start": 71.047, "dur": 1.346, "text": "So what is the way to choose optimal path?"}, {"start": 72.793, "dur": 2.607, "text": "How should"}, {"start": 75.447, "dur": 1.126, "text": "router find out."}, {"start": 76.607, "dur": 2.586, "text": "How router finds out"}, {"start": 79.44, "dur": 3.493, "text": "whether to send it to N1,to N2 or to N3 or"}, {"start": 83.173, "dur": 2.054, "text": "to N4.How does it find out?"}, {"start": 85.647, "dur": 1.233, "text": "By routing tables."}, {"start": 87.0, "dur": 2.087, "text": "Here comes the concept of routing tables."}, {"start": 89.12, "dur": 1.973, "text": "Basically what is routing table?"}, {"start": 91.453, "dur": 1.447, "text": "It is collection of entries."}, {"start": 93.18, "dur": 1.067, "text": "That what is happening inside"}, {"start": 94.307, "dur": 1.446, "text": "my network"}, {"start": 95.787, "dur": 1.453, "text": "All the values in my network"}, {"start": 97.513, "dur": 1.627, "text": "are contained in"}, {"start": 99.22, "dur": 1.413, "text": "my routing table."}, {"start": 100.7, "dur": 1.007, "text": "It is basically"}, {"start": 101.767, "dur": 1.18, "text": "a to and fro"}, {"start": 103.2, "dur": 1.513, "text": "communication."}, {"start": 105.493, "dur": 1.12, "text": "Meaning what is happening"}, {"start": 106.667, "dur": 2.54, "text": "inside the complete network. Which connection is working."}, {"start": 109.247, "dur": 1.006, "text": "Which connection is not working."}, {"start": 110.32, "dur": 1.913, "text": "From which one network to which"}, {"start": 112.267, "dur": 1.193, "text": "other network it has to go."}, {"start": 113.493, "dur": 1.36, "text": "From which node to other node it has to go."}, {"start": 115.233, "dur": 1.047, "text": "What is my cost?"}, {"start": 116.5, "dur": 1.373, "text": "All these points are"}, {"start": 117.947, "dur": 1.273, "text": "under routing table."}, {"start": 119.244, "dur": 1.756, "text": "And how is routing table"}, {"start": 121.024, "dur": 1.349, "text": "created? To properly create a"}, {"start": 122.373, "dur": 1.1, "text": "routing table either"}, {"start": 123.513, "dur": 1.794, "text": "we can make a"}, {"start": 125.407, "dur": 1.253, "text": "static routing table"}, {"start": 126.7, "dur": 1.18, "text": "or dynamic."}, {"start": 128.2, "dur": 1.567, "text": "What is a static routing table?"}, {"start": 130.153, "dur": 1.007, "text": "Meaning manually."}, {"start": 131.46, "dur": 2.66, "text": "One that is created manually. You have to"}, {"start": 134.16, "dur": 2.153, "text": "manually insert data in routing table."}, {"start": 136.613, "dur": 2.4, "text": "And who has to do it? Network Administrator will do it"}, {"start": 139.3, "dur": 2.64, "text": "This is possible in a small network."}, {"start": 142.22, "dur": 2.327, "text": "Enter the data manually."}, {"start": 144.58, "dur": 1.007, "text": "What a person is connected with?"}, {"start": 145.78, "dur": 1.287, "text": "What is the underlying cost?"}, {"start": 147.1, "dur": 1.027, "text": "What is the delay?"}, {"start": 148.407, "dur": 1.526, "text": "But if we talk about internet."}, {"start": 150.007, "dur": 1.82, "text": "Everything is possible"}, {"start": 151.86, "dur": 1.007, "text": "on internet."}, {"start": 152.973, "dur": 1.867, "text": "Everything is possible means."}, {"start": 154.92, "dur": 1.013, "text": "Rather than using static"}, {"start": 156.213, "dur": 1.1, "text": "we work"}, {"start": 157.373, "dur": 1.007, "text": "on dynamic."}, {"start": 158.427, "dur": 2.286, "text": "Our routing table should"}, {"start": 161.033, "dur": 3.094, "text": "automatically send information to each other."}, {"start": 164.373, "dur": 1.787, "text": "And they should be"}, {"start": 166.333, "dur": 1.707, "text": "automatically updated."}, {"start": 168.28, "dur": 2.26, "text": "So how is a dynamic routing table created?"}, {"start": 170.813, "dur": 1.64, "text": "To make them we use"}, {"start": 172.487, "dur": 1.166, "text": "routing"}, {"start": 173.707, "dur": 1.786, "text": "protocols."}, {"start": 175.533, "dur": 1.867, "text": "We use different type of routing protocols."}, {"start": 177.653, "dur": 2.554, "text": "What are they? They are set of instructions, rules"}, {"start": 180.54, "dur": 1.253, "text": "which help"}, {"start": 181.88, "dur": 1.627, "text": "routers"}, {"start": 183.54, "dur": 1.233, "text": "to share data."}, {"start": 185.0, "dur": 1.36, "text": "And after sharing"}, {"start": 186.393, "dur": 1.747, "text": "update"}, {"start": 188.407, "dur": 1.046, "text": "your routing table."}, {"start": 189.493, "dur": 1.167, "text": "From time to time."}, {"start": 190.693, "dur": 1.96, "text": "Because if any packet comes"}, {"start": 192.687, "dur": 1.486, "text": "That packet, on the basis of"}, {"start": 194.207, "dur": 1.006, "text": "routing table"}, {"start": 195.267, "dur": 1.86, "text": "could be checked"}, {"start": 197.18, "dur": 1.493, "text": "for the direction in which it should be sent."}, {"start": 198.913, "dur": 1.814, "text": "So it reaches"}, {"start": 200.76, "dur": 1.253, "text": "its destination"}, {"start": 202.053, "dur": 1.007, "text": "on the network as soon as possible."}, {"start": 203.313, "dur": 2.46, "text": "So the routing protocols that we have."}, {"start": 206.227, "dur": 1.626, "text": "There are different type of routing protocols."}, {"start": 208.207, "dur": 1.006, "text": "Intra domain and"}, {"start": 209.26, "dur": 1.007, "text": "inter domain."}, {"start": 210.407, "dur": 2.393, "text": "So how does this intra domain and inter domain works."}, {"start": 213.1, "dur": 3.553, "text": "As we all know. Internet is a very big term."}, {"start": 216.953, "dur": 1.18, "text": "Meaning internet is a very big term."}, {"start": 218.18, "dur": 1.033, "text": "What we call"}, {"start": 219.527, "dur": 1.646, "text": "this big area."}, {"start": 221.213, "dur": 2.1, "text": "What do we call this complete network. Internet."}, {"start": 223.64, "dur": 1.393, "text": "But internally we have divided"}, {"start": 225.093, "dur": 1.22, "text": "internet into"}, {"start": 226.653, "dur": 1.06, "text": "autonomous systems."}, {"start": 228.727, "dur": 1.82, "text": "Autonomous systems means that the"}, {"start": 230.94, "dur": 2.793, "text": "particular network. Let's say"}, {"start": 233.793, "dur": 1.007, "text": "it is a collection of different networks."}, {"start": 235.32, "dur": 1.313, "text": "Like there is one network N1,"}, {"start": 236.993, "dur": 1.007, "text": "N2,"}, {"start": 238.12, "dur": 1.007, "text": "N3,"}, {"start": 239.213, "dur": 1.007, "text": "N4."}, {"start": 240.293, "dur": 1.834, "text": "There are different networks that are"}, {"start": 242.16, "dur": 1.207, "text": "connected to networks and each other."}, {"start": 243.4, "dur": 1.613, "text": "And what is autonomous system"}, {"start": 245.047, "dur": 1.386, "text": "One autonomous system"}, {"start": 246.48, "dur": 1.16, "text": "is one that"}, {"start": 247.74, "dur": 1.413, "text": "is under one particular"}, {"start": 249.187, "dur": 1.006, "text": "network administrator."}, {"start": 250.407, "dur": 2.553, "text": "Meaning, the network under"}, {"start": 253.02, "dur": 1.073, "text": "one particular network administrator"}, {"start": 254.127, "dur": 1.5, "text": "we call it"}, {"start": 255.66, "dur": 1.327, "text": "autonomous system"}, {"start": 257.06, "dur": 1.56, "text": "Let's say, if we talk about Delhi."}, {"start": 258.653, "dur": 1.787, "text": "Under Delhi,"}, {"start": 260.473, "dur": 1.107, "text": "all the complete networks."}, {"start": 261.733, "dur": 1.127, "text": "All the small small networks."}, {"start": 262.9, "dur": 1.913, "text": "After connected them together."}, {"start": 264.907, "dur": 1.633, "text": "Complete Delhi could be"}, {"start": 266.573, "dur": 1.567, "text": "called autonomous system."}, {"start": 268.173, "dur": 1.94, "text": "Similarly if we talk,"}, {"start": 270.147, "dur": 2.62, "text": "let's say Bombay. Mumbai also has its"}, {"start": 272.807, "dur": 2.173, "text": "own autonomous system."}, {"start": 275.033, "dur": 1.007, "text": "Under different autonomous systems"}, {"start": 276.14, "dur": 1.813, "text": "how does the communication occur."}, {"start": 278.227, "dur": 2.753, "text": "That is known as inter domain. Meaning, this is one autonomous system."}, {"start": 281.013, "dur": 3.36, "text": "This is another autonomous system. How would they communicate with each other."}, {"start": 284.413, "dur": 1.854, "text": "How will"}, {"start": 286.353, "dur": 1.34, "text": "they share data."}, {"start": 287.933, "dur": 2.167, "text": "How will they share routing information"}, {"start": 290.36, "dur": 1.047, "text": "That is the inter domain."}, {"start": 291.64, "dur": 1.36, "text": "And Intra domain is"}, {"start": 293.3, "dur": 1.893, "text": "within one autonomous system."}, {"start": 295.273, "dur": 1.394, "text": "Meaning inside one autonomous system."}, {"start": 296.74, "dur": 1.027, "text": "one autonomous system."}, {"start": 298.107, "dur": 3.12, "text": "Like, I gave the example of Delhi."}, {"start": 301.467, "dur": 1.133, "text": "Let's say I want to send information"}, {"start": 302.633, "dur": 1.74, "text": "from Hauz Khas to green park."}, {"start": 304.713, "dur": 2.174, "text": "We are talking about a simple example."}, {"start": 306.92, "dur": 1.88, "text": "If we want to do routing within"}, {"start": 308.833, "dur": 1.007, "text": "an autonomous system."}, {"start": 310.34, "dur": 1.32, "text": "Meaning"}, {"start": 311.893, "dur": 1.007, "text": "within the autonomous system,"}, {"start": 312.933, "dur": 2.174, "text": "we want to share data."}, {"start": 315.14, "dur": 1.007, "text": "Different routers"}, {"start": 316.18, "dur": 1.007, "text": "want to share data."}, {"start": 317.507, "dur": 1.193, "text": "That how much is the cost."}, {"start": 318.927, "dur": 1.066, "text": "Which net is running."}, {"start": 320.027, "dur": 1.78, "text": "Which link is basically not working."}, {"start": 322.04, "dur": 1.573, "text": "All this"}, {"start": 323.687, "dur": 1.053, "text": "status,"}, {"start": 324.773, "dur": 1.04, "text": "how does that status"}, {"start": 325.847, "dur": 1.053, "text": "is shared,"}, {"start": 327.167, "dur": 1.006, "text": "with the help of"}, {"start": 328.373, "dur": 1.467, "text": "intra domain. That's why"}, {"start": 330.54, "dur": 3.0, "text": "it is intra. And inter means between the autonomous system."}, {"start": 333.593, "dur": 2.86, "text": "Under intra domain"}, {"start": 336.507, "dur": 1.66, "text": "we have distance vector"}, {"start": 338.2, "dur": 1.847, "text": "and link state routing."}, {"start": 340.08, "dur": 1.82, "text": "And how do we implement distance vector."}, {"start": 342.213, "dur": 1.807, "text": "RIP."}, {"start": 344.053, "dur": 1.007, "text": "RIP is a real life protocol."}, {"start": 345.287, "dur": 2.82, "text": "That is a routing information protocol that we generally use"}, {"start": 348.373, "dur": 3.294, "text": "to share information in intra domain."}, {"start": 351.887, "dur": 1.353, "text": "Similarly, there is OSPF,"}, {"start": 353.533, "dur": 1.234, "text": "that is open shortest"}, {"start": 355.127, "dur": 2.593, "text": "path first. And this basically works"}, {"start": 357.8, "dur": 1.007, "text": "on link state routing."}, {"start": 358.98, "dur": 1.44, "text": "Similarly we have border gateway protocol."}, {"start": 360.453, "dur": 1.747, "text": "It works on"}, {"start": 362.267, "dur": 1.493, "text": "path vector."}, {"start": 364.54, "dur": 1.007, "text": "But if you are preparing for gate,"}, {"start": 365.58, "dur": 2.08, "text": "net or any other exam."}, {"start": 367.72, "dur": 2.393, "text": "Even if you are preparing for college or university level exam."}, {"start": 370.48, "dur": 1.84, "text": "Then remember distance vector"}, {"start": 372.647, "dur": 2.086, "text": "is the most important."}, {"start": 374.82, "dur": 1.627, "text": "The very important algorithm."}, {"start": 376.733, "dur": 2.1, "text": "That is a distance vector. After that we"}, {"start": 378.867, "dur": 1.86, "text": "sometimes talk about link state routing."}, {"start": 380.773, "dur": 1.72, "text": "Here this is ."}, {"start": 382.567, "dur": 1.006, "text": "the major portion"}, {"start": 383.64, "dur": 1.553, "text": "And all the three algorithm's,"}, {"start": 385.227, "dur": 1.14, "text": "all the three protocols"}, {"start": 386.647, "dur": 1.366, "text": "works on"}, {"start": 388.073, "dur": 2.74, "text": "unicasting. The meaning of unicasting."}, {"start": 390.847, "dur": 1.52, "text": "We generally use unicasting or multicasting."}, {"start": 392.413, "dur": 1.74, "text": "Meaning if we want to do one to one"}, {"start": 394.36, "dur": 2.993, "text": "communication. One person want to send data to the other person."}, {"start": 397.7, "dur": 2.493, "text": "Or multicasting, meaning"}, {"start": 400.227, "dur": 1.006, "text": "I want to send data to a full group."}, {"start": 401.367, "dur": 1.42, "text": "Or multicasting, meaning"}, {"start": 402.827, "dur": 1.006, "text": "Then there are different protocols for multicasting."}, {"start": 404.0, "dur": 1.127, "text": "These protocols are"}, {"start": 405.167, "dur": 1.233, "text": "under unicasting."}, {"start": 406.447, "dur": 1.14, "text": "This is basically"}, {"start": 407.853, "dur": 1.007, "text": "basic information"}, {"start": 408.94, "dur": 1.033, "text": "of routing protocols."}, {"start": 410.247, "dur": 1.36, "text": "Next we will discuss"}, {"start": 411.64, "dur": 1.173, "text": "one by one that what is a distance vector"}, {"start": 412.86, "dur": 1.44, "text": "and how does it work."}, {"start": 414.613, "dur": 1.174, "text": "Thank you."}]}